12 The commission shall minimize the approval of sub-precincts and not impose a strict
13 mathematical formula on the population deviation for municipal precincts unless the creation of
14 a sub-precinct is required to meet a plus or minus 10 per cent population deviation for municipal
15 representative districts.
16 The commission shall provide the state secretary with the meeting notice and minutes of
17 all commission meetings, which shall be posted on the secretary’s website.
18 The commission shall provide the state secretary an electronic geographic information
19 system shapefile or equivalent containing the population of every city and town ward, precinct
20 and sub-precinct within the boundaries of the approved congressional, councillor, senatorial and
21 representative districts and an ASCII compatible file containing a written description of all
22 changes in the municipality, ward, precinct and county description of each approved
23 congressional, councillor, senatorial and representative districts as will be reported by the
24 secretary pursuant to section 133 of chapter 54 no later than 30 days after the final approval by
25 the governor of the enacted decennial division and shall be posted on the secretary’s website.
26 The state secretary will maintain and update any subsequent changes to city and town
27 ward, precinct and sub-precinct and shall post those changes on the secretary’s website.
28 The state secretary shall establish, implement and maintain an internet portal on the
29 secretary’s website to display and access commission records including but not limited to
30 commission meeting notices, meeting minutes, votes approving municipal ward, precincts and
31 sub-precincts, geographic information system shapefiles of approved voting districts,
32 congressional, councillor, senatorial and representative district descriptions by municipality,
33 including ward and precinct for any municipality split into multiple representative districts, and a
